Content:

Shiva Kovil (no. 1) of Ancient Polonnaruwa
Shiva Kovil (no. 1) is the first kovil you will come across after entering the ancient city of Polonnaruwa. The walls of this kovil are made out of a closely fitted stone blocks of a type which is not found anywhere near Polonnaruwa. The carvings of the Gods of this kovil are of Indian style and it is thought that these carved stones are  probably brought from India or done by Indian Artists who came to Sri Lanka.
